Product name: Copper Bone Dog Tag for Dogs - Personalized Dog Tag - Pet ID Tag - Dog Name Tag - Custom Dog Collar Tag - Puppy Tag - Metal Pet Tag - Buster
Description:
This adorable bone-shaped dog tag is sure to get your pet noticed!  The tag is made of solid copper, which makes it very sturdy but still light enough for medium and large dogs.  The ID tag measures about 1.25 inches long and 1 inch wide at its widest point.  For scale, this pet ID is slightly smaller than two U.S. quarters lined up next to each other.  
Each tag will be customized with your pet's name and phone number.  I can use the large font (as shown in the photos) for names up to 7 characters only!  If your pet has a longer name, I can make the tag with a smaller font.  The name will then be about the same size as the phone number.
Please note: This tag can only be stamped on the front side. I cannot put the phone number on the back of the tag. Because stamping is deeper than engraving, stamping on the back side will show through and mar the front of the tag. 
After your tag has been personalized, I give it a brushed antique finish and then seal it with a durable clear sealant to slow down the aging of the copper.  Two stainless steel heavy-duty split rings come installed, so it will be ready for your pet to wear right away.
I hand stamp each piece a single letter at a time, which makes each tag absolutely unique.  Stamping is much deeper than engraving.  This is great for pet tags because these tags will remain readable even after crazy puppy antics.
**IMPORTANT ORDERING INFORMATION**
In the "Notes to Seller" section, please be sure to include:
1) Your pet's name (limit 7 characters for the large font and 12 characters for smaller font)
2) Phone number you would like on the tag
Please note:  Due to differences in computer monitors and phone screens, the color of your pet tag may appear slightly different in the picture than the tag you receive.  The tag is made of copper and is a copper color and then is given an antique finish, which slightly darkens it.
Thanks for visiting Heartland Stamp Company.  Be sure to favorite my shop to see my new designs as they're added to my shop!

Product name: Sample Pack Catnip Cat Toys - All Proceeds Donated
Description:
This is a sample pack of my different catnip cat toys.  I started out years ago by making small toys ( about 1.5" in diameter), with bells and ribbon.  Then I found that my cats were losing these toys under the appliances and furniture.   Enter the larger size toys (about 2.5" in diameter), with bells and ribbon.  Some of my repeat customers have mentioned they would like toys without bells/ribbon.  Their nocturnal playing cats have batted toys around the house, causing hours of lost sleep for their owners!  hee hee.  Ok, so then I started making the larger toys with no bells and ribbon.  The next item I designed is using baby alpaca yarn, which is one of the softest things on earth - and created a larger toy, (approximately 3" in diameter).  Finally, I thought about the ultimate cat toy - a crocheted ball filled with nothing but catnip!
With this order, you get one of each: a small toy with NO BELL OR RIBBON; a large toy with NO BELL OR RIBBON; a large toy WITH BELL AND RIBBON; a large baby alpaca toy; and a toy with nothing but catnip. Please allow me to choose colors for you.

Product name: Handwriting Guide for Journals and Planners / Dot Grids PDF - 3 Uppercase, 1 Lowercase, 1 Practice Dot Grid sized for 5mm grids - Lettering
Description:
Use this handwriting guide to improve your handwriting for bullet journaling. These are easy to use. Just print and start tracing. Use the space at the bottom of each guide to practice on your own.
These printable guides are placed on a dot grid that matches the popular  Leuchtturm1917 dot grid. This is key because it allows you to practice improving your writing with the correct sizing! Learn to write within 1x1, 1x2 and 2x2 boxes.
This is the basic font that I use for a majority of my writing in my bullet journal. These guides will help you achieve consistency in your writing and improve muscle memory. Once you master this, you can play around with adapting the letters to your own style!
------
5 page guide includes:
1) Lowercase handwritten font. Each letter fits within a 1x1 box.
- Perfect for everyday writing.
2) Uppercase handwritten font. Each letter fits within a 1x1 box.
- Perfect for short lists and everyday writing.
3) Uppercase handwritten font. Each letter fits within 1x2 boxes.
- Perfect for long headers.
4) Uppercase handwritten font. Each letter fits within 2x2 boxes.
- Perfect for short headers.
5) Blank dot grid that can be used for practice.
- Use for practicing!
Check out my Number Handwriting Guide as well!
https://www.etsy.com/listing/512573621/number-handwriting-guide-for-bullet
------
Notes:
- You can slip these guides or the blank guide behind notebook pages for easy tracing. Just use a dark pen/marker to outline guide and slip behind the page you want to write on!
- Box sizes are measured in width x height (ex: 1x2 = 1 box wide by 2 boxes high)
- This is a printable PDF guide. You will need to unzip the file to access the 5 different PDFs.
-----
For personal use only; do not distribute.

Product name: Kokomo Cream Natural Deodorant - Handmade Creamy, Dreamy Tropical Organic- 4.75 oz With Recipe
Description:
Crunchy Betty's Natural Market BEST SELLER!
Take yer pits on a fresh, dreamy tropical vacation from stink every day of the year!
I formulated Kokomo Cream handmade deodorant with ingredients that will help protect you from odor, while you remain fresh as a breeze all day long.
All 4.75 oz of deodorant cream (which is at least twice as much product as a store-bought deodorant) contains specialized ingredients like neem oil (antibacterial and healing), lime essential oil (deodorizing, refreshing, and antibacterial), tea tree oil (deodorizing and antibacterial), and coconut oil (nourishing and highly antibacterial), as well as other excellent ingredients you'd expect to find in a high-quality handmade deodorant cream.
And, as always, with your order of a full-size product from Crunchy Betty's Natural Market, you'll receive the exact recipe I used to create your yummy goods. This way, you can recreate it at home (and reuse the amber glass container, even!) if you'd prefer to try your hand at crafting your own body products.
Note: This is not an antiperspirant (your body was naturally designed to sweat - stopping that process is a no-no). 
Unlike many other homemade deodorants, this contains arrowroot powder instead of cornstarch, which is less potentially irritating - and you know it's not GMO!
INGREDIENTS: Cold pressed organic coconut oil, arrowroot powder, naturally procured (mined instead of chemically created) baking soda, neem oil, mango butter, lime essential oil, tea tree essential oil, sweet orange essential oil, and a small amount of beeswax to help your cream retain its consistency.
---
SPECIAL NOTE ON HANDMADE DEODORANT: 
First, it's very important to give your body a small amount of time (at least a week or two) to adjust from using commercially produced deodorant to natural deodorant. During this time, you may experience some irritation as your body adjusts and releases the synthetic chemicals it is accustomed to.
(This period is WORTH IT if you stick it out - nothing feels better than knowing you're avoiding the iffy ingredients in store-bought deodorant.)
However, a small percentage of people are unable to adjust to using baking soda under their arms. If an itchy irritation persists, discontinue use of this deodorant.
This handmade deodorant has a shelf life of at least 8-10 months.
---
IMPORTANT NOTE FOR THE SUMMER: During warmer months, your Kokomo Cream may melt and separate a little. This is totally okay, and the deodorant is still in perfect working shape. All you have to do is give it a good stir to combine before using. (Personally, I prefer it this way, because it goes on extra super silky smooth.) In addition, it is highly likely that, after sitting in a hot delivery truck all day, it will reach you in this melty state. If you want to reset and harden it, just give it a good stir and leave it (closed tightly) in the refrigerator for 1-2 hours.
--
FEATURED ON CRUNCHY BETTY:
Kokomo Cream handmade deodorant is entirely based on the deodorant I use, and was inspired by my very first experiment with homemade deodorant (which is still my very favorite deodorant ever). 
You can read more about the process here:
http://www.crunchybetty.com/all-roads-lead-to-the-pits-homemade-deodorant
http://www.crunchybetty.com/all-roads-lead-to-the-pits-the-homemade-deodorant-conclusion
There's a recipe there if you want to try it yourself, or buy the Kokomo Cream to find out if you like handmade deodorant first - and then make it yourself when you're out! 
---
THIS LISTING: Is for 4.75 oz of handmade Kokomo Cream deodorant, which should be enough to last at least two months or more, in an amber glass container (p.s. never put essential oils in plastic containers), as well as the recipe for Kokomo Cream deodorant.
Happy pits!

Product name: Organic Acne Fighting Facial Serum - Acne Treatment - Organic Acne Serum - Organic Face Oil - Vegan Face Oil
Description:
"Wait a second, wait a second, WAIT A SECOND. You want me to put OIL on my acne-prone skin?!?!"
In all likelihood, that's the question you just screamed at me into your computer screen. Thankfully, the technology to transfer that scream from your computer to mine hasn't been invented yet (please, gods of tech, let it never be). So, since you're likely sitting there wondering what the actual *ahem* I'm thinking, let me explain. 
Forget everything you know. Oil is GOOD for you. You should consider cleaning your face with it, and then slapping some more on once you've rinsed that lot off. 
*ducks flying shoe*
No seriously, I mean it! Go ahead and look up "the oil cleansing method" and let your mind be blown. In short: acne is a complicated condition which can involve food allergies, hormones, skin irritants, lack of proper hydration…you get the gist. It's a long list. While it's sometimes unclear what may be causing your acne, what is clear is that most mass-produced facial cleansers contain harsh, toxic ingredients that strip the skin of the natural oil (sebum) it secretes to keep itself moisturized and protected. So what does your skin do in response? Freaks out and produces more oil to replace what's been stolen away, leading to greasy looking skin, more clogged pores, and a continuation of a vicious cycle.
Then you have the store-bought lotions that follow these cleansers. When you get right down to it, they're nothing but oil (likely mineral oil or animal fats - which your skin is less likely to recognize and absorb), alcohol, water, and a slew of chemical emulsifiers and preservatives meant to blend all of that together and extend its shelf-life to some unnatural (and frankly terrifying) number of years. 
By cleansing your skin with oil, you're adhering to one of the basic principles of chemistry: like dissolves like. By moisturizing with naturally-derived plant-based oil, you're skipping over all those chemical additives and getting straight to the point of it all - MOISTURIZING YOUR SKIN.
This recipe contains the following: 
Organic Cold-Pressed Jojoba Oil: Widely considered to be the oil (or wax, since it technically is one) that most closely resembles sebum. Because of this, it's absorbed more easily than any other carrier oil and won't clog up your pores.
Organic Cold-Pressed Grape Seed Oil: Rich in linoleic acid, antioxidant and anti-inflammatory properties, this oil is perfect for combating some causes of acne and wonderful for treating that which may already have formed. 
Organic Cold-Pressed Neem Oil: Antibacterial, antifungal, antihistamine, need I say more? Okay, I will. This oil has been used in traditional Ayurvedic practices to treat acne for centuries. 
Organic Steam Distilled Lavender, Rosemary, and Tea Tree Essential Oils: Because of lavender's antimicrobial and antioxidant properties, it helps to prevent the bacteria buildups that can lead to breakouts. Paired with the antimicrobial and antiseptic qualities of Rosemary Essential Oil and the antibacterial powerhouse that is Tea Tree Essential oil, this blend is ideal for treating acne and helping to prevent scars from forming once it retreats.
Use with our Acne Fighting Face Mask and Acne Fighting Facial Toner to really kick those breakouts to the curb:
https://www.etsy.com/listing/397806095/acne-fighting-face-mask-vegan-face-mask
https://www.etsy.com/listing/451764004/acne-fighting-facial-toner
Packaged in a recyclable glass bottle with a compostable label and shipped in recycled, recyclable packaging so you can feel good about what's inside AND outside your product. 
                                                                                                     **A FEW NOTES**
- A little goes a long way with this serum. To use, dispense a small dollop onto the palm of your hand both morning and night and rub into clean skin, avoiding mouth and eye areas. No one knows your skin like you do, so this use description is more of a "suggestion". A starting point, if you will. If you feel that your skin is still a little dry after application, simply add more oil. Easy as that! 
- The neem oil used in this product contains naturally occurring particulates which haven't been filtered out because I believe it's more beneficial to the finalized product to leave them in. So be aware that upon use there might be some plant matter in your glass dropper. It should also be noted that neem oil has an odor that not everyone will find pleasant, and this scent is not entirely masked by the essential oils used this recipe. 
- Those pregnant or breastfeeding should not use this blend, as the side effects of many essential oils are not fully known due to lack of clinical testing. 
- This is an all-natural product made with sterilized equipment and no natural or chemical preservatives. For best results, store in a cool, dark place (a bathroom cabinet works perfectly) and use within six months of purchase. Clean, dry fingers or an organic, unbleached cotton ball are best to apply this serum. The glass of the dropper should not touch your skin and should be placed directly back into the glass jar after use, as adding dirt or water to any preservative-free beauty product could introduce some yucky bacteria into the mix. 
PRO TIP: if a natural product looks or smells off, discontinue use.
*For external use only. Keep out of reach of children. Discontinue use if irritation occurs. This information has not been evaluated by the FDA. This product is not intended to diagnose, treat, cure, or prevent any disease.

Product name: Farewell Fungus Salve
Description:
Yo, I love to talk about foot fungus. The more I learn about bacteria and fungi, the more I weirdly admire them. Like plants and animals, they are the other creatures populating the heck out of the world out there! 
Bacteria and fungi have had dynamic relationships with medicinal plants for, like, millions of years. When we use plants as medicine, our bodies get to be the stadium of this ancient game. The ‘antiseptic’ and ‘anti-fungal’ properties of plants we apply in herbal medicine are borrowed from the plant’s own ability to keep bacteria and fungus at bay. 
Let me just take a moment to thank the medicine plants for letting me borrow some of their stuff- I will totally return that phone charger asap btw.
Foot fungus is an especially stubborn variety- in a way similar to a dude who won’t move out of his parents house. You know, I’ll just chill way down here between your toes/basement. Why would I leave? You got the space and you feed me regular meals. Years go by. Oh yeah, still totally down there.
Well, Fat and the Moon has an herbal smackdown/life coach squad here to help you get your basement back so you can finally put your pinball machine down there. 
Herbs like black walnut, chaparral, thuja and usnea ain’t fooled by the fungus’ empty promises of flight from feet! 
To compare and contrast for a moment with the Healing Foot Powder… in a salve, the herbs are infused in oil making the product especially good for the dry and itchy variety of fungus- Athlete's foot being at the top of that list. The oil soothes the dry and cracking parts of the skin while delivering the kick in the pants to the offending fungi. The Foot Powder is great for the fungus that loves the sweaty scene, since the powder absorbs moisture. They can be used in tandem if you have some 'all seasons' fungus that just won’t quit..
The Farewell Fungus Salve can also be used for fungus on other parts of the bod and would be great for stinkers like ringworm. Don’t even get me started on ringworm…..
2 fl oz

chaparral*, black walnut hull*, oregon grape root*, wild crafted usnea infused sunflower oil*, beeswax, essential oils of tea tree* & thuja*

Product name: The Etsy Seller's Simple Guide to Taxes, PDF eBook, instant download, tax forms, tax documents, business planner, tax information, IRS
Description:
*** The term "Etsy" is a trademark of Etsy, Inc. This product is not affiliated with Etsy, Inc. ***
New Etsy shop owner? When you began selling on Etsy, you may not have considered the tax rules associated with your new shop. Now it's tax time, and you have no idea what to do! Enter the Etsy Seller's Simple Guide to Taxes. Don't let tax concerns take away from the fun of making and crafting. With this easy to read guide you can quickly understand small business taxes to save you time and money! (This guide is for U.S. tax payers.)
After reading this book you will know:
-If your handmade business or Etsy shop is a hobby or a business
-What business structure to choose
-How to register your business with your state and the IRS
-Basic business recordkeeping
-Easy tax deductions you can take as a product seller
-What tax form to file as a product seller
-Detailed information on filing Schedule C
-Easy tax deductions you can take on your tax return
-How to take a home office tax deduction
-How to take a business mileage tax deduction
-How to tax a tax deduction for your computer or camera
-How to take an inventory and calculate your cost of goods sold
-What income to record as revenue
-If you need to pay self employment tax
-And much more!
This book is for you if you want to save time and money completing your small business tax return!
This easy read guide is almost 60 pages of helpful information!
Updated for your 2016 tax forms!
Running an Etsy shop, creating handmade products, or selling other products should be fun! Don't let taxes make you worried. Quickly understand all you need to know about taxes as a product seller so you can spend your time focusing on what you love most . . . . crafting and selling!
Why trust my advice? I'm an accountant and an Etsy Seller! Been there, done that! You can find more useful information on my website:  www.SmallBusinessSarah.com    When you sign up for my newsletter you will get a free Small Business Start-Up Checklist!

Product name: Stargazing at Noon - Poetry Chapbook by Amanda Torroni - 38 pages
Description:
"Stargazing at Noon by Amanda Torroni is charged with flickering, unapologetic undercurrents. The primitive, dreamlike consistency offers a lucid depth that's both relatable and other-worldly. She talks up close about the distance between us. She writes at the edge of things in a lyrical, unobstructed way that's both inventive and nostalgic. The dizzying pace and acute awareness reminds me of a meteor shower itself--a rare sensory experience, breath-catching and unforgettable. I was free-falling through these pages. They'll make anyone wish they understood the mysteries of the past, the ever-expanding universe, the human condition as well as she does." -Review by Megan Magers
"Stargazing at Noon" is Amanda Torroni's first poetry chapbook, featuring 30 of her best poems from the last year.  Book size is 6"x9".  Cover art by Kathleen Rule.  40 pages.
Thank you for your continued love & support!

Product name: HELENA  Black guipiere lace kimono - getting ready bridal kimono, valentines day, lingerie, trousseau, honeymoon, Valentine's Day gift
Description:
Hello!
I’m Anna, and I’m a designer and dressmaker based in Worthing, near Brighton. I design and make every garment here in my studio at the seaside for my bridal wear label; ‘This Modern Love’. 
The aesthetic for ‘This Modern Love’ is romantic, feminine, bohemian and beautifully simple garments, all hand crafted using the finest materials such as silk chiffon, corded lace, duchess satin and soft tulle.
❤️ HELENA - Guipiere lace kimono - Lingerie ❤️
Made with 100% soft guipiere lace in black with a black satin ribbon tied at the waist.
Model wears a black bodysuit with the kimono - the kimono is a sheer/see through design with a floral, embroidered motif all over . 
Loose fit sleeves and pretty scalloped detailing at the hem, plus a pretty grosgrain ribbon to tie the kimono. Ribbon available in champagne or black - whichever you prefer.
The standard size fits most and is approximately 35 inches from shoulder to hem. The sleeves are 11 inches wide. This can be made in any size, please let me know your bust waist, hips measurement & desired length if you would like a different size to the standard.
How does ordering work?
This kimono is handmade to order, in any size. The standard size (pictured on the model who is a sz 8/10 and 5ft 11 tall) fits most, but if you have special requirements, tall or petite etc just let me know.
That’s it! Your lace kimono will be shipped to you within 2 weeks and I’ll let you know when it’s on it’s way - you can follow my social media accounts for updates on what I’m working on.
Can I visit you?
Yes! You’re very welcome to visit my home studio to try on the range of sample dresses and view the fabric sample books and range of laces available in person. Please contact me to make an appointment. 
If you’re unable to visit me then you’re welcome to order online! I can answer any questions you have and discuss your design ideas with you over email.
Made to order
Please bear in mind that the kimonos are made to order and for that reason are non returnable and non refundable. I offer a free fitting on every garment, so that if you find it needs a minor alteration to be ‘fitted’ (i.e. taken in) then this service is provided free of charge. I’m afraid that I cannot alter a dress to be made larger or longer where incorrect measurements have been provided. If you’re unsure about how to take your measurements please do get in touch and I’m happy to help.
Like to know more?
You can read more about my designs, highlights, background, FAQs and testimonials from real brides on my website & take a look at my portfolio of work on my social media too on Wordpress, Pinterest, Facebook, Instagram & Twitter.
www.thismodernlovebridal.com
Anna
x

If ordering a piece with the Swarovski crystal, the aqua blue (March) crystal will be used as a default. The "Timothy & Leslie) example is shown with a sapphire (September) crystal. Want to change the color? Please refer to the Swarovski crystal color chart on this listing and include the color crystal in the special instructions/note to seller box during checkout. 
This is an authentic British Sixpence with Elizabeth II on the reverse side of the coin. Each Six Pence comes with a blue Swarovski crystal on a white ribbon to tie to your bouquet. **I only carry white ribbon in stock. You can easily remove and replace the ribbon included with the color of your choice once you receive your bouquet charm.** Or remove the coin and crystal from the ribbon to place the coin in the bride's left shoe for good luck.
Each coin and crystal are attached by a silver stainless steel jump ring and can easily be converted to a keepsake necklace or bracelet after the wedding day. The disc is a 1" stainless steel round pendant.  Perfect for the bride or a bridesmaids gift. 
The dates range on the coins in this listing. Most are from the 1950's to 1960's and are in good, but circulated condition. We do not polish the coins to look new. Each coin has been on a journey, and we do not wish to remove the character and luck each coin has experienced. 
WHY WE DON'T PERSONALIZE THE BACK...all of our items are hand stamped using a hammer and a metal punch to make an impression in the metal. This can sometimes leave a slight smudge mark on the reverse. For this reason, we never recommend stamping on the front and the back of an item. 
This item is ~hand made.~ Our studio has these pieces punched by a local metal company, and we hand stamp all of the lettering in our studio. Each letter is hand aligned and punched into the metal, so the placement of the wording will vary slightly from piece to piece. 
Please check our Shop Announcement for current processing times. We strive to ship personalized items as quickly as possible (usually 1-3 business days). **Processing times may change during holidays (Valentine's Day, Mother's Day, Father's Day, and Thanksgiving - Christmas holiday season.**
**Shipping: ~Please read our shipping policy carefully.~ First Class mail is the slowest delivery and least expensive. Priority mail is faster and a little more expensive. Both shipping options are available during checkout for delivery inside the United States. International shipping is unpredictable, and once the package leaves the United States - I can not see the tracking information or give you updates. All tracking numbers for domestic and international orders are uploaded to your purchases page once your item is shipped. You can estimate shipping time to your area on the USPS website. I am shipping from NC zip code 28465.**

Product name: 70 PRE-CUT Custom Clothing Labels {Colorfast/Fray-proof/Iron-on/Sew-in}
Description:
******At Last... PRE-CUT labels.******  ****Now with High Pigment Ink*****
*****INTERNATIONAL ORDERS are sent without tracking to keep rates down for you.  Your rate includes up to 7 sets of labels, any more - please contact us for a special listing.****
FAQ LIST HERE:  https://theheartofwonder.patternbyetsy.com/about
Your order details may be typed in the NOTES to SELLER section during checkout.  =) 
You've asked often, here they are for 2017.  Printed, cut, paper backing removed and ready-to-go.  Pre-cut Teeny-Tiny branding labels are made with 100% cotton, are completely washable and colorfast as well as fray-proof. These labels are heat sealed and can be ironed in and/or sewn in.  Labels measure 1/2 " high x  1.75 " wide.    There are TWO fabric choices: White Cotton and Cotton Muslin, please see photo #4. Labels are soft and flexible, nothing scratchy.  Proofs are sent upon request via Etsy convo after payment. Order specifics may be typed in the Note to Seller section at checkout or sent via Etsy message. 
IRONING IN:  
We use Heat n Bond, an ultrahold, permanent fabric adhesive.  Your labels will have this flexible, rubbery backing.  If you're not sewing the labels in, ironing instead, they need only a brief touch with a hot, dry iron to stay in place.  Allow them to cool.  Do not take repeat passes with the iron.  The backing is a permanent fabric adhesive that will last through many washes.  When ironed in properly, the labels will stay in for a long time without sewing. Over time a corner may curl a bit, but this is the normal wear-and-tear process in exchange for the no-sew convenience. 
SEWING IN:  
The bonded backing on the labels will pass through under a sewing machine needle just fine, as well as by hand.  The labels may be ironed after sewing in as well.  
TEXT information:
Two lines are optional, please see listing photos as one line will be smaller.  Up to 18 characters/spaces are recommended; text will get smaller and smaller with added characters and/or drop to two lines. Text color is black.  This can be changed, however we advise using the darkest colors possible to retain clear legibility for small fonts.   There is no extra charge for colored fonts.  Default font used is "Cambria Math." Please note any changes in font style when ordering, you may list a number from the font choice image, see photo #5.  If I do not have the font you prefer, please request and I'll see what I can do.  =) 
LOGO IMAGES:
If you'd like your personal logo added.  Please send your logo via etsy conversation.  Crop/edit your image as close to the basic shape of you label as possible before sending.  The image should be sharp and crisp and in JPEG or PNG format. Overcompensate on color when creating your image as images print lighter on fabric then on paper - the fabric absorbs more ink. Also, consider darker images if choosing muslin fabric, as muslin lends a more natural, earthy look  - images print softer. 
USAGE AND CARE: 
Machine wash, tumble dry low/delicate. We use high pigment ink and labels will retain high color. The labels will not fray easily as they are heat sealed with a permanent adhesive backing. If there are any strings from the production process, just snip them away.  They are not frays, just an occasional part of the process here in the studio. 
PER SHEET information:
This listing is for one {1} PRE-CUT, set of 70 labels, one design type per sheet.  Each set of labels is created, printed and treated right here in our shop when you order. **Increasing or decreasing individual label size will change amount of labels per sheet on custom orders. Larger labels means less labels per sheet/**  If you change the size, we'll fit as many per sheet as possible. No need for a special listing for this. Also, there are extra labels in each order to account for any printing imperfections.
PROCESSING/Shipping information:
Please allow us up to, but no more than, 1-3 business days handling time before shipping.  Labels ship USPS first class mail in a kraft envelope with a packing invoice. You will receive shipping notice via Etsy.  Orders with proof requested will NOT ship until proof has been approved. Proofs are sent via Etsy message so, check back.  =) These specifics include international orders as well. 
***PLEASE REMEMBER TO PURCHASE EXPEDITED SHIPPING*** if your labels are a rush for a special event, especially if I'm creating a new template for sizing for you.  Orders take 1-3 business days to process here in the shop.  Also plan for time to apply your labels before your event.  =)
***BULK ORDERS*** Please just message me if you need multiple sets of labels and are concerned about time frames or shipping, always willing to help.

Product name: 1lb Unrefined Shea Butter, Wholesale, Certified Fair Trade, Certified Organic, Wholesale, Bulk
Description:
One pound (1lb) of bulk pure of organic unrefined shea butter for lotion making, soap making, hair care and skin care. Shea butter is a great addition to any soap, skin and hair care products. Use it in your formulations to reap all the benefits of this natural, healing, moisturizer. 
WHY BUY OUR SHEA BUTTER?
- Our shea butter is USDA certified organic.
- Our shea butter is Fair Trade USA certified fair trade.
- We have a long history of selling pure shea butter on Etsy with many satisfied customers. See our feedback.
- Astrida Naturals sells only fair trade unrefined shea butter. Fairly traded shea butter is obtained from a source that pays the African women who manufacture the shea a fair price for the product, allowing the women to support themselves, their families, and their communities.
Our Shea Butter is extracted from the Karite (Shea) Nut in Ghana using traditional West African methods that do not utilize chemicals during processing. Because this shea butter is unrefined it retains the highest concentration of healing and moisturizing benefits for raw use or in skin and hair care formulations.
To use in formulas heat very slowly in a double boiler to melt. To prevent grittiness cool rapidly or mix well into formulas while still warm.
Please note, this is a natural product. Color variances may occur but this does not in any way affect the quality of the product.
NEED MORE SHEA?
Larger quantities are available please contact me for details.
How does Shea Butter benefit my skin and hair?
Regular use of unrefined Shea Butter produces softer, smoother healthier skin and is safe for all skin types. Shea Butter is a natural source of vitamins A, E, and F. These antioxidants help the skin to retain its natural elasticity, absorb moisture from the air, and help prevent premature wrinkles by boosting collagen production.
Shea Butter contains natural UV sun protection that is estimated to be around an SPF 6. Daily use of Shea Butter on the face and body reduces sun exposure, which in turn slows down the appearance of aging. Shea Butter also acts as a natural mantle against elements of cigarette smoke, smog and chemical pollutants in the atmosphere.
Shea Butter can also help your hair. It provides moisture to dry or damaged hair from the root to tip, repairing and protecting against weather damage, dryness and brittleness. It also absorbs quickly and completely into the scalp to rehydrate without clogging pores. It is beneficial for processed and heat-treated hair, and is an excellent treatment for dry scalp.

Product name: Minimalist Silver Ear Cuff Non Pierced, Conch Cuff Earring Stack, Sterling Silver Earring Cuff No Piercing, Ear Stack, Fake Conch Ring
Description:
Sterling silver ear cuff with studded texture. You can buy a single, or a pair for stacking.
This is a non pierced earring. I love these as a way to get the look of extra piercings and extend the party up your ear.
Check out this ear cuff in a super stack:
https://www.etsy.com/listing/502514363/set-of-3-stackable-sterling-silver-ear
The ear cuff has an inner diameter of 10 millimeters, and an opening of 4 millimeters. It is adjustable and fits best in the "conch" position, where the cartilage meets the lobe.
Handmade by me from .925 sterling silver. It has polished, rounded ends for easy sliding on and off. The  silver has a bright, shiny finish.
You will receive the ear cuff in a semi-annealed state, that is to say the sterling silver is malleable enough that you can adjust it to fit your ear. If no adjustments are needed, that is also great, because it is sturdy as is.
To make the ear cuff smaller (fit tighter), pinch the ends together between your fingers. To enlarge it, I recommend sliding it down the barrel of a pen or marker that has a larger graduated diameter to gently force the ends apart. If you need any guidance, just contact me!
If you are new to ear cuffs, I find the best way to put one on is to hook it around the cartilage ridge at the top of your ear and then slide it down while gently rotating it over the inside ridge. Once you adjust your cuff for the perfect fit, you will be able to slide it on and off with ease every time, there is no need to open and close it.
Model is wearing a sample earring. You will receive brand new earrings.
Product photos were taken on a macro setting to show details. Please reference scale photos and measurement listed above.
This is adult jewelry. It is not intended for children 14 and under.
